 class="ͼe">LabelEncoder</span><span>()</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">xlabel</span><span>[</span><span class="ͼe">col</span><span>] </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">le</span><span class="ͼ8">.</span><span>fit_transform(</span><span class="ͼe">xlabel</span><span>[</span><span class="ͼe">col</span><span>]</span><span class="ͼ8">.</span><span>astype(</span><span class="ͼe">str</span><span>))</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">label_encoders</span><span>[</span><span class="ͼe">col</span><span>] </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">le</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="483" data-end="486">
<h3 data-start="488" data-end="541" data-section-id="xmq345">🔍 What this code does (important for interview):</h3>
<ul data-start="543" data-end="765">
<li data-start="543" data-end="607" data-section-id="1d5boip">
<p data-start="545" data-end="607"><strong data-start="545" data-end="561">LabelEncoder</strong> converts categorical data into numeric form</p>
</li>
<li data-start="608" data-end="675" data-section-id="dmvgl2">
<p data-start="610" data-end="675">Loop runs for each column (<code data-start="637" data-end="644">model</code>, <code data-start="646" data-end="660">transmission</code>, <code data-start="662" data-end="672">fuelType</code>)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="676" data-end="765" data-section-id="aexjb3">
<p data-start="678" data-end="765">Stores encoder for each column in <code data-start="712" data-end="728">label_encoders</code> (useful later for inverse transform)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="767" data-end="770">
<h3 data-start="772" data-end="813" data-section-id="1u9j8hc">⚠️ Important Concept (Interview Trap)</h3>
<p data-start="815" data-end="854">👉 Label Encoding assigns numbers like:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="855" data-end="897"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-f8sla627.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none; max-height: 433px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>Petrol = 0</span><br><span>Diesel = 1</span><br><span>Electric = 2</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="899" data-end="970">But ML models may think:<br>
👉 Electric &gt; Diesel &gt; Petrol (which is WRONG)</p>
<hr data-start="972" data-end="975">
<h3 data-start="977" data-end="1010" data-section-id="11hlmhc">✅ When to Use Label Encoding:</h3>
<ul data-start="1011" data-end="1104">
<li data-start="1011" data-end="1063" data-section-id="yl5pgy">
<p data-start="1013" data-end="1063">Tree-based models (Random Forest, Decision Tree) ✅</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1064" data-end="1104" data-section-id="1gqsb3z">
<p data-start="1066" data-end="1104">Not good for Linear Regression / KNN ❌</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1106" data-end="1109">
<h3 data-start="1111" data-end="1126" data-section-id="1r6lx44">🔥 Pro Tip:</h3>
<p data-start="1127" data-end="1178">If no order exists → use <strong data-start="1152" data-end="1178">OneHotEncoding instead</strong></p>
<hr data-start="1180" data-end="1183">
<p data-start="1185" data-end="1328" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">If you want, I can:<br>
