<h3 data-start="598" data-end="625" data-section-id="1wly020"><span role="text">2. <strong data-start="605" data-end="625">LinearRegression</strong></span></h3>
<ul data-start="626" data-end="713">
<li data-start="626" data-end="692" data-section-id="1srcc83">
<p data-start="628" data-end="692">A machine learning model used for predicting continuous values</p>
</li>
<li data-start="693" data-end="713" data-section-id="1ql19ha">
<p data-start="695" data-end="713">Based on equation:</p>
</li>
</ul>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">y = mx + b</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.625em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">y</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mord mathnormal">x</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">+</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">b</span></span></span></span></span>
<p data-start="733" data-end="745">👉 Used for:</p>
<ul data-start="746" data-end="788">
<li data-start="746" data-end="766" data-section-id="1nks7hs">
<p data-start="748" data-end="766">Price prediction</p>
</li>
<li data-start="767" data-end="788" data-section-id="8cl1sr">
<p data-start="769" data-end="788">Sales forecasting</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="790" data-end="793">
<h3 data-start="795" data-end="824" data-section-id="4z9it6"><span role="text">3. <strong data-start="802" data-end="824">Evaluation Metrics</strong></span></h3>
<h4 data-start="826" data-end="862"><span role="text">✅ <strong data-start="833" data-end="862">mean_absolute_error (MAE)</strong></span></h4>
<ul data-start="863" data-end="916">
<li data-start="863" data-end="893" data-section-id="1md6rr2">
<p data-start="865" data-end="893">Average of absolute errors</p>
</li>
<li data-start="894" data-end="916" data-section-id="i8h21">
<p data-start="896" data-end="916">Easy to understand</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="918" data-end="929">👉 Formula:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac><mo>∑</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">∣</mi><msub><mi>y</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub><mo>−</mo><msub><mi>y</mi><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">∣</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">MAE = \frac{1}{n} \sum |y_{true} - y_{pred}|</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.10903em;">M</span><span class="mord mathnormal">A</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">E</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 2.0074em; vertical-align: -0.686em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.3214em;"><span style="top: -2.314em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">n</span></span></span><span style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span style="top: -3.677em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">1</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.686em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mop op-symbol large-op" style="position: relative; top: 0em;">∑</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mord">∣</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">y</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">r</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">e</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">−</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.0361em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">y</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3361em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">re</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">d</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mord">∣</span></span></span></span></span>
<hr data-start="982" data-end="985">
<h4 data-start="987" data-end="1022"><span role="text">✅ <strong data-start="994" data-end="1022">mean_squared_error (MSE)</strong></span></h4>
<ul data-start="1023" data-end="1072">
<li data-start="1023" data-end="1072" data-section-id="zlwjwq">
<p data-start="1025" data-end="1072">Squares the error (penalizes large errors more)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1074" data-end="1085">👉 Formula:</p>
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac><mo>∑</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>y</mi><mrow><mi>t</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub><mo>−</mo><msub><mi>y</mi><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow></msub><msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">MSE = \frac{1}{n} \sum (y_{true} - y_{pred})^2</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.05764em;">MSE</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 2.0074em; vertical-align: -0.686em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 1.3214em;"><span style="top: -2.314em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">n</span></span></span><span style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span style="top: -3.677em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">1</span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.686em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.1667em;"></span><span class="mop op-symbol large-op" style="position: relative; top: 0em;">∑</span><span class="mopen">(</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">y</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight" style="margin-right: 0.02778em;">r</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">e</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.15em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">−</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1502em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.03588em;">y</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.3361em;"><span style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0359em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">re</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">d</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose"><span class="mclose">)</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8641em;"><span style="top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>
<hr data-start="1140" data-end="1143">
<h4 data-start="1145" data-end="1175"><span role="text">✅ <strong data-start="1152" data-end="1175">r2_score (R² Score)</strong></span></h4>
<ul data-start="1176" data-end="1231">
<li data-start="1176" data-end="1213" data-section-id="119wuc6">
<p data-start="1178" data-end="1213">Measures how well model fits data</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1214" data-end="1231" data-section-id="1sd9u9j">
<p data-start="1216" data-end="1231">Range: 0 to 1</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1233" data-end="1251">👉 Interpretation:</p>
<ul data-start="1252" data-end="1292">
<li data-start="1252" data-end="1273" data-section-id="1sal7ko">
<p data-start="1254" data-end="1273">1 = perfect model</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1274" data-end="1292" data-section-id="w7ktgo">
<p data-start="1276" data-end="1292">0 = poor model</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1294" data-end="1297">
<h1 data-start="1299" data-end="1339" data-section-id="316kck">🎯 How to Explain in Interview (Short)</h1>
<p data-start="1341" data-end="1545">“I used train_test_split to divide data into training and testing sets. Then I trained a Linear Regression model and evaluated its performance using MAE, MSE, and R² score to measure prediction accuracy.”</p>
<hr data-start="1547" data-end="1550">
<h1 data-start="1552" data-end="1564" data-section-id="179mj0e">🔥 Pro Tip</h1>
<p data-start="1566" data-end="1613">If interviewer asks:<br>
👉 “Which metric is best?”</p>
<p data-start="1615" data-end="1622">Answer:</p>
<ul data-start="1623" data-end="1720">
<li data-start="1623" data-end="1652" data-section-id="cvfqk7">
<p data-start="1625" data-end="1652">MAE → easy interpretation</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1653" data-end="1685" data-section-id="565jyc">
<p data-start="1655" data-end="1685">MSE → penalizes large errors</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1686" data-end="1720" data-section-id="18sjj5u">
<p data-start="1688" data-end="1720">R² → overall model performance</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1722" data-end="1725">
<p data-start="1727" data-end="1870" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">If you want, I can:<br>
