<h1 data-section-id="lo907p" data-start="3373" data-end="3407">🎯 What You Can Say in Interview</h1>
<p data-start="3409" data-end="3644">👉<br data-start="3411" data-end="3414">
“I enhanced my Streamlit application UI by integrating Tailwind CSS via CDN, creating a modern card-based design, improving user experience with responsive layouts, and adding visually appealing components for better interaction.”</p>
<hr data-start="3646" data-end="3649">
<h1 data-section-id="1esd6q4" data-start="3651" data-end="3697">⚠️ Important Reality (Interview Smart Point)</h1>
<p data-start="3699" data-end="3768">If interviewer asks:<br>
👉 “Does Streamlit support Tailwind officially?”</p>
<p data-start="3770" data-end="3777">Answer:</p>
<ul data-start="3778" data-end="3853">
<li data-section-id="1pzmp6t" data-start="3778" data-end="3799">
<p data-start="3780" data-end="3799">❌ No (not natively)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1muu3rd" data-start="3800" data-end="3853">
<p data-start="3802" data-end="3853">✅ But can be integrated using HTML + CDN workaround</p>
</li>
</ul>
