<hr data-start="1240" data-end="1243">
<h1 data-section-id="vbz1g1" data-start="1245" data-end="1263">🎯 Interview Tip</h1>
<p data-start="1265" data-end="1309">If asked:<br>
👉 “How did you run your project?”</p>
<p data-start="1311" data-end="1466">Say:<br>
“I used VS Code, created a virtual environment, installed dependencies using pip, and ran the Streamlit app using the command <code data-start="1442" data-end="1464">streamlit run app.py</code>.”</p>
<hr data-start="1468" data-end="1471">
<h1 data-section-id="77ebrh" data-start="1473" data-end="1486">🔥 Pro Tips</h1>
<ul data-start="1488" data-end="1623">
<li data-section-id="vvkgai" data-start="1488" data-end="1534">
<p data-start="1490" data-end="1534">Use <strong data-start="1494" data-end="1513">Python 3.9–3.11</strong> (best compatibility)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="crwu8b" data-start="1535" data-end="1574">
<p data-start="1537" data-end="1574">Keep <code data-start="1542" data-end="1548">.pkl</code> files in same directory</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1coax36" data-start="1575" data-end="1623">
<p data-start="1577" data-end="1623">Always use <code data-start="1588" data-end="1606">requirements.txt</code> for deployment</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1625" data-end="1628">
<p data-start="1630" data-end="1799" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">If you want, I can:<br>
